        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/eada6e/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2010-05-12T20:07:42.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I just checked Farr Vintner\u2019s website and they are offering the 2009 Roc de Cambes for 440 lbs (about $50 per).  Thus, it is looking more and more like we are going to see high pricing for the upper tier wines (e.g., Barton/Poyferre at $80-$100 per on initial release).  Further, I notice a number of U.S. stores (Zacky\u2019s, Calvert-Woodley, Binny\u2019s, Wine Exchange) buying heavy at the low end.  Wonder how well these wines will sell.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 8,
