        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/eada6e/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2010-05-13T17:51:40.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Yes, this wine fits more squarely into the $25-$30 price category.  I see the price as a sign that well regarded wines, like the 2009 Lynch Bages, Leoville Poyferre, Barton, and Pavie Macquin, will likely open well above what past vintages have cost.  Makes the 2009 Bordeaux campaign somewhat anticlimatic for many of us with modest resources.</p>",
